## End-of-Development Checklist — MUST Show to User

When a development task is complete (feature shipped, code generated, tests written), the agent MUST end its response with a copy-pasteable checklist that the developer ticks off before running locally. The checklist MUST include — at minimum — these items, customised to what was added:

```
## Before you run locally — please complete:

- [ ] Open `.env` and replace ALL `replace-with-real-value` placeholders with real credentials:
      - SFDC_USERNAME
      - SFDC_PASSWORD
      - SFDC_SECURITY_TOKEN
      (and any other secrets added this session)
- [ ] Confirm `.env` is gitignored (run: `git check-ignore .env` — should print `.env`)
- [ ] In Anypoint Code Builder: open `global-configs.xml` → click each connector config → Test Connection
- [ ] Hit F5 (or Run > Start Debugging) → pick "Run Mule App (with .env)"
- [ ] Wait for `DEPLOYED` in the log (~60–90s)
- [ ] Smoke-test endpoints with Invoke-RestMethod (see commands below)

## Smoke-test commands
(...PowerShell Invoke-RestMethod for each new endpoint...)
```

Tailor the checklist to the actual work done in that session — drop items that don't apply, add items for new connectors / endpoints / env vars introduced. The variable list under "replace placeholders" MUST match exactly what's in `.env`.

If the session did NOT add any new secrets and `.env` already has real values, the checklist may skip the placeholder-replacement step but should still surface the connection test + smoke test.

